Int ' l Kite Flying Festival Held in Hong Kong
HONG KONG , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- More than 3,000 Hong Kong people enjoyed different shapes and colors of kites flying high in the sky Sunday at the one-day International Kite Flying Festival .
This year the festival attracted teams from Beijing , Xi ' an , Kagoshima of Japan , Macao , Malaysia , the Philippines and Singapore to contest in the international competition , according to Tony Kan , vice-chairman of the Provisional Regional Council which co-organized the festival .
Apart from the international competition , members of the public were given chances to send up kites under the guidance of instructors .
To promote the popular recreational event with a long history , Hong Kong Post issued a set of four special stamps starting Sunday .
